section.def:
Director
                (署長) means the Director of Electrical and
            Mechanical Services;

record
                (紀錄冊) means the record kept under section
                14;

subparagraph.content:
the date on which the new calculation method will take effect
                                (effective
                                date);

paragraph.content:
the relevant information is submitted before the
                    commencement*
                    of sections 4 and 5;

subparagraph.content:
the particulars of the product model, including but not limited to its
                        brand name, model name, energy efficiency and performance characteristics as
                        declared by the registration holder;

section.def:
non-ducted
                            (非管道式) means not having any
                        additional ductings or pipes required for air intake and exhaust;

paragraph.content:
is intended to be installed with mounting rods or mounting bolts
                            fastened on the ceiling in accordance with the manufacturer’s
                            installation procedures;

in which a secondary fluid or absorbent, rather than a
                                mechanical compressor, is used to circulate the
                                refrigerant;

subparagraph.content:
a refrigerated surface (commonly known as an
                                        evaporator) that condenses moisture from the
                                        atmosphere;

section.def:
heating unit (加熱單元), in relation to a product, means a part of the product
                        with independent heating function on which a countertop container can be
                        placed;

paragraph.content:
that uses the light-emitting diode technology, but not the
                                organic light-emitting diode technology, to emit light;
                                and

section.def:
lamp cap (燈頭), in relation to a product, means a part of the product that
                        connects the product to a lamp-holder or lamp connector for
                        electricity;

burner (燃燒器),
                        in relation to a product, means a part of the product that mixes gas with
                        air for combustion;

paragraph.content:
a product is of built-in type if it is designed to be installed in
                            a hollow of a similar size as the product in a kitchen worktop;
                            and

that is a domestic gas appliance as defined by regulation
                                    2 of the Gas Safety (Installation and Use) Regulations
                                    (Cap. 51 sub. leg. C);

the energy label is to be encircled by a blank border that is at least
                        2 mm wide, and it must not cover more than 50% of the surface area of the
                        largest side of the product packaging;
